title: Blinken Meetings With French Officials Yield No ‘Concrete Actions’ to Strengthen Ties
sub_head: Relations between the two countries have soured following last month’s announcement of security pact among U.S., U.K. and Australia
body:
PARIS—U.S. Secretary of State Antony Blinken continued his efforts to repair the relationship with the nation’s oldest ally, holding a series of meetings with French leaders that yielded promises to deepen cooperation, but no specific commitments.
Mr. Blinken met Tuesday with French President Emmanuel Macron and Foreign Minister Jean-Yves Le Drian, as well as national security adviser Emmanuel Bonne.
